        </header>
        <main>
            <div class="question">
                <h2 class="question">What's a Table?</h2>
                    <p id="pullquote">A table represents information in grid format. 
                        Examples of tables include financial reports, TV schedules
                        and sports results.
                    </p>
            </div>
            <div id="tags">
                <h2>Table Tags</h2>
                <table>
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                        <th>Tag</th>
                        <th>Name</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                        </tr>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="code"><span>&lt;table&gt;</span></td>
                            <td>Table</td>
                            <td>The &lt;table&gt; element is used to create a table. The contents of the table are written out row by row. </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="code"><span>&lt;thead&gt; or &lt;th&gt;</span></td>
                            <td>Table Head</td>
                            <td>The &lt;thead&gt; element is used to represent the header for either column or row</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="code"><span>&lt;tbody&gt;</span></td>
                            <td>Table Body</td>
                            <td>The &lt;tbody&gt; contains the set of rows that make up the table data</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="code"><span>&lt;tr&gt;</span></td>
                            <td>Table Row</td>
                            <td>The table row container. You indicate the start of each row with &lt;tr&gt; and is followed by the &lt;td&gt; elements.</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="code"><span>&lt;td&gt;</span></td>
                            <td>Table Data</td>
                            <td>Each cell is represented using a &lt;td&gt; element.</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="code"><span>&lt;tfoot&gt;</span></td>
                            <td>Table Footer</td>
                            <td>The footer of the table belongs in the &lt;tfoot&gt; element.</td>
                        </tr>
                        
                    </tbody>
                    </thead>
                </table>
            </div>
            <div id="attributes">
                <h2>Table Attributes</h2>
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <th>Attribute</th>
                            <th>Name</th>
                            <th>Description</th>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="code"><span>colspan</span></td>
                                <td>Column Span</td>
                                <td>Defines how columns a &lt;td&gt; element should span.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="code"><span>rowspan</span></td>
                                <td>Row Span</td>
                                <td>Defines how many rows a &lt;td&gt; element should span.</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                        </table>
            </div>
            <div class="footer">Made by Lauren L. of MoonBean Labs.</div>
